social_posts.post_text: If it feels like I've been saying "bye" to this apartment for months now, it's because I have. Turns out everything takes longer than expected when you buy a new house and have to move your entire life for the first time in over a decade. We will be moved out before Christmas, which means I don't have it in me to decorate for the holidays this year. I hung lights in my windows a couple of weeks ago because it's amazing what twinkly artificial lighting can do for my mental health during these short, dark days. Trying to grasp on to joy where I can this holiday season, but everything feels like a whirlwind and I wish I could just push fast forward to Christmas.

From 2012-2021 we hosted a Christmas Party/White Elephant Ornament Exchange, and let’s be honest, the annual photo booth was the main event. 

Shared here in chronological order is a selection from each year - with a bonus at the end from the very first year we hosted, when friends decided to launch themselves on to the bed for some sweet mid-air captures. 

These really were the best of times in that apartment. 🎄

Our annual Shmister Christmas + Cousin photos from our White Elephant ornament exchange party. 

Pictured here from 2021-2012 🎅🏼

It was truly impossible to pick favorites, and even more impossible to get every attendee represented in these Christmas Party round-up posts. I love everyone who ever attended one of these parties we hosted - basically the Only party we hosted each year. Maybe I’ll print them all in to a silly little holiday coffee table book, because seeing these faces brings me such joy.

In 2020 I received a small art grant from the City of LA to create work while staying ‘Safer At Home.’ I reached out to a few of the bartenders I knew who were also out of work at the time and asked if they had some cocktail recipes they could share with me, I had the intention to keep this project going and eventually turn it in to a book. I’d still love to make that happen, even if its concept has shifted post-pandemic.

So, if you’re a bartender - professionally or not, and have a recipe or two that you’d like to see conceptualized into a cool looking photo, slide in to my DMs! Let’s chat, I want to start this personal project back up again. Too many people are drinking bad drinks at home, let’s help them out with something better. 😉🍹

Featured here is the Oceanfront, a cocktail by @brandonhardyy:

- Barspoon 1:1 Simple Syrup
- 3/4oz Grapefruit Juice
- 1/2oz Lemon
- 1/2oz Orgeat
- 1/2oz Aperol
- 2oz Plymouth Gin
- Light Sprinkle of Cinnamon

Shake with ice. Fine strain up.  Cinnamon stick garnish.

Chana Masala is one of my favorite dishes to make, and this cocktail recipe is a great way to use the chickpea juice you usually dump out of the can. I started this cocktail project while everyone was staying home at the start of the pandemic, so I wanted to photograph cocktails people could easily make themselves. 

If the egg whites in sours give you the ick, or if you’re vegan, or if you just like to use up all your ingredients when you cook - garbanzo bean juice, or aquafaba is an excellent alternative!

Whiskey Sour:
- Egg white OR 1/2oz Aquafaba 
- 3/4oz Lemon
- 3/4oz Simple Syrup
- 2oz Bourbon 
Dry shake, then shake with ice and strain in to a coupe. Garnish with drops of Angostura Bitters. 

Once again, I’m asking if there are any bartenders out there who have a cocktail recipe or two they’d like to share with me! I’d love to keep photographing more drinks and make a colorful cocktail book. So many cocktail recipe books I’ve seen are very dark, sleek, and moody - I want to create some bright and funky cocktail images. 

Cheers! 🍸

Calling all bartenders and cocktail enthusiasts! I’d love to continue photographing cocktails - if you’ve got a favorite recipe or two you’d like to share, can be something unique and fancy or classic and simple. Spread the word, tell a friend. 😉

I’ve already shared this image, but it was one of my favorites from the first round of drinks I shot. 

The Caballo Viejo by @tishtaylorla:

- 1/4oz Green Chartreuse 
- 3/4oz Sweet Vermouth 
- 2oz Uno, Dos, Tres Tequila Anejo (or another dark anejo) 
Stir with ice and strain in to a coup glass. Garnish with a flamed grapefruit peel.

This image from Lisbon is one of my favorite photos. I used it on one of my first promos, and it’s now available for the first time as a print in my newly launched print shop! 

I started with a selection of my travel photos, because I feel so grateful for all of the places around the world I’ve been able to experience, and seeing all of the images together in one gallery reminds me of this. 

Over the next few weeks I’ll be combing through my library and releasing different projects in the online store - so if there’s any images of mine that you always thought would look good on your wall, let me know! 

Check out the link in my bio for the first 20 prints I have available.

I finally opened an online print store!!! I’ve launched with a selection of my favorite pictures from around the world.

My trip to Peru in 2017 was one of the most incredible trips. The people, the colors, the landscape! This image is from the top of a mountain we hiked for lunch, with the best view of Lake Titicaca.

Add a pop of color to your walls - framing options are available. 

laurenlemon.darkroom.com - or click the link in my bio. 🌸

I’ve made a new collection available in my Print Store! 

This time some of my favorites from my on-going Chromalogical Order series. 

Check out laurenlemon.darkroom.com, or click the link in my bio to see what’s available to print. Add some color to your walls, while supporting a small artist!

This series of images was originally made for the #chromachroma art show a decade ago in San Francisco, curated by @bsterling, featuring work by @jimmymarble and I. The framed prints then lived a whole other life on display in the @wetransfer office in Venice, Los Angeles. 

Now available again as individual prints, although I recommend picking up the whole series - because they look great together. Check out laurenemon.darkroom.com, or click the link in my bio to visit my print shop. I’ve made a lot of my all-time favorite photos are finally available to purchase. 

❤️🧡💛💚💙💜🖤

These images, and others from my #chromalogicalorder series, are now available in my print store. Visit laurenlemon.darkroom.com to see framing and pricing options. 

Also, I appreciate all the feedback and conversations about AI I’ve been having in response to the images I posted in my stories. It’s been exciting to try something new and get a bit wild with my imagination, but I can also see what a valuable tool it can be in my regular workflow as well. Go take a peek if you haven’t already. 😉

I appreciate those who have contacted me to inquire if these messages were credible, and for letting me know. 

If you would like to work together, please email or DM and I can follow up in an official manner.

Last Fall @gogrey and I bought ourselves a house in the desert, and we’ve spent the last year living out here and making it our home. Packing up and leaving the neighborhood I loved for over a decade in Los Feliz was hard, but everyday I wake up here, I get to see the landscape and the big sky - I know this is the right place for us to be. I love having a home where our friends and family can come stay with us, and I couldn’t be more grateful for the community who has welcomed us too. Year 1 down, many more to go, and our own little Bunny Ranch is only going to keep getting better. ❤️
Between Christmas and New Year: time doesn’t matter, and there are too many sweets sitting around.

Last Night (of the year)’s Party! NYE 2004 @the.tiny.pony!!!!!!! 

We rang in the New Year dancing to blog-house and wearing our very best Indie Sleaze fashion. We took shots of Sparks, and pretended we’d wake up feeling 20 years younger as well. I had a blast running around the party with my camera, bringing me back to my photography roots. 😜 Here’s to another year, and here’s to feeling good all the time! 🎆

All the NYE photos are on my Flickr, link in bio.

I recently learned that Gen Z loves the movie LA LA Land, so I figured I’d reshare these images I took of Ryan Gosling and Emma Stone backstage at the 89th Academy Award Show - you know, to appeal to the kids these days. 

These were taken when the film won the Oscar for Best Cinematography, and the first photo won myself and @theacademy a Communication Arts award that year. ✨ Still one of my absolute dream-come-true jobs.
